title: My Heart and Lute
creator: Thomas Moore
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 12 recordings of My Heart and Lute by Thomas Moore . This was the Weekly Poetry project for December 12th, 2010. "My Heart and Lute" is a song/poem by Thomas Moore. In Through the Looking-Glass by Lewis Carroll, Alice recognizes the tune ("My Heart and Lute") used in the song called Haddocks' Eyes sung by the White Knight. (Summary by Wikipedia) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, and for further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; poetry; romance; music
